Package cz.syntea.common.cfg Description

Internally used in the Syntea projects.
NOTE: this class doesn't provide any kind of namespace support and there are other limitations connected with SYNTEA projects. The user can use those methods AS IT IS without any kind of warranty.

MsgX

Contains a collection of methods used in Syntea Queue engine and in the other parts of Syntea projects. The MsgX object can be created either in "write" or "read" mode (see MsgX). The incomming data are java.lang.String objects containing the XML form (read mode). In "write" mode the XML object is constructed (see newElement(String), putRootAttribute(String,String), putAttribute(String,String), putAttribute(String,String), addElement() etc). X-definitions are used for validation and for integritiy checking of data. If an error occurs an exception is thrown.
